02/08/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- EU Commissioner for Justice and Home Affairs Franco Frattini praised Justice Minister Monica Macovei and Administration and Home Affairs Minister Vasile Blaga on Tuesday (1 August) for concrete measures undertaken in areas most critical to Romania's EU accession. Wrapping up a two-day visit, Frattini said the country is on the right track in terms of implementing judicial and security reforms required for EU entry on 1 January. At the same time, he called on local authorities to step up efforts to rid the judiciary of even the appearance of corruption. (Ziua, Azi, Nine o'clock - 02/08/06)
